{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1781683036,"nonce":"V9BSTcv576uaFLv51J+xKp+Hn+Y=","title":"No connection pooling abstraction","message":"There is no pool abstraction anywhere in the workspace (no deadpool/bb8/sqlx::Pool usage). The Connection / ConnectionWithTransaction traits in `crates/squealy/src/connection.rs` operate on a single owned connection.\n\nReal applications need pooled connections. Decide between:\n- integrating an existing pool (deadpool / bb8) in the backend crates, vs\n- a small pool trait in core that backends implement, so the query builder can acquire/release around execution.\n\nShould compose with the existing transaction() closure API so a transaction borrows a pooled connection for its duration. Likely a backend-crate concern (squealy-postgresql / squealy-mysql) with at most a thin core trait.","files":null}]}